all-packages.description:
The &lt;b&gt;Hashing&lt;/b&gt; library.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
A hash function is any algorithm or subroutine that maps large
data sets of variable length, called keys, to smaller data sets
of a fixed length.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
This library only implement non-cryptographic hash functions.
&lt;br&gt;
